docs.abstract: Thanksgiving — like the rest of life — just isn’t the same through a screen.
docs.snippet: Thanksgiving — like the rest of life — just isn’t the same through a screen.
docs.lead_paragraph: At the end of September, the Centers for Disease Control posted a list of recommendations for how Americans can safely celebrate Thanksgiving this year. Eat all the pie you want (but only with your immediate family). Attend parades and big games (but only on TV). Shop till you drop (from the couch). Skip the flight back home (Zoom with your relatives instead). Give thanks (while maintaining social distance).

headline.main: The Future Was Supposed to Be Better Than This

docs.abstract: Dustin Johnson won the Masters at 20 under, five strokes ahead of Australia’s Cameron Smith and Sungjae Im of South Korea.
docs.snippet: Dustin Johnson won the Masters at 20 under, five strokes ahead of Australia’s Cameron Smith and Sungjae Im of South Korea.
docs.lead_paragraph: Dustin Johnson won the 2020 Masters and set a scoring record at 20 under par, two strokes better than the former record, held jointly by Tiger Woods and Jordan Spieth. Johnson, who grew up an hour away, in South Carolina, became the first world No. 1 to win the event since Woods in 2001.

headline.main: The 2020 Masters: Dustin Johnson Sets Scoring Record

docs.lead_paragraph: The protests that broke out after the police killing of George Floyd in May were some of the biggest racial justice marches organized in decades. In the early weeks, polling showed broad and deep support for them across the country.

docs.abstract: Narrowing the candidate pool may not lead to the diverse representation the incoming administration is seeking.
docs.snippet: Narrowing the candidate pool may not lead to the diverse representation the incoming administration is seeking.
docs.lead_paragraph: President-elect Joe Biden has made assembling a diverse team a priority. He also faces pressure from the progressive wing of his party to limit corporate influence on hires for his administration, avoiding candidates from Wall Street or company boardrooms. But narrowing the candidate pool that way won’t help create a more representative administration, some suggest.

headline.main: Could Limiting Corporate Candidates Hurt Biden’s Diversity Push?

docs.abstract: And what else you need to know today.
docs.snippet: And what else you need to know today.
docs.lead_paragraph: Every November, after the editors of The Times Book Review have wrapped up their big end-of-year issues, they immediately turn their attention to the following year. They start by creating a working list of nominees for the next iteration of 100 Notable Books — the one that will be published almost a year later.

docs.abstract: Yet Philadelphia, Milwaukee and Detroit have become the targets of G.O.P. allegations of voting shenanigans.
docs.snippet: Yet Philadelphia, Milwaukee and Detroit have become the targets of G.O.P. allegations of voting shenanigans.
docs.lead_paragraph: In Pennsylvania, much of President Trump’s attention since the election has focused on Philadelphia, where he has baselessly insisted there is a “mountain of corruption.” In Michigan, litigation by Mr. Trump’s campaign has concentrated on Detroit, where Republican poll watchers say they felt intimidated by election workers in Black Lives Matter apparel. And in Wisconsin, legal challenges and rumors have circled around Milwaukee, where one internet conspiracy  theory turns on a briefly misplaced flash drive of election results.

headline.main: The Cities Central to Fraud Conspiracy Theories Didn’t Cost Trump the Election
headline.print_headline: Conspiracy Theories Center on Cities That Didn’t Cost Trump the Election
